sh colony. His tenure as Kenya’s second president was plagued by corruption and nepotism. (DW) Vanguard Nigeria News The retired President of Kenya, Mr Daniel Arap Moi, has been discharged from Ichilov Hospital in Tel Aviv, Israel, where he had gone for medical check-ups. March 16, 2018 In "News" The son of Kenya's founding president and a man who epitomises the country's elite, Uhuru Kenyatta hopes to win a second and final five-year term in elections on August 8. August 5, 2017 In "News" Kenyan environmental activist Wangari Maathai, the first African woman to be awarded the Nobel Peace Prize, has died of cancer at the age of 71, her family announced Monday. September 26, 2011 In "News"